WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:05.337
<i> "the liberty report"</i>
<i> with sally langston.</i>

00:05.339 --> 00:07.606
Welcome back,
lovers of liberty.

00:07.608 --> 00:10.376
It's impeachment week
here at "the liberty report,"

00:10.378 --> 00:13.012
And, boy,
do we have a treat for you.

00:13.014 --> 00:15.948
Starting today,
18 senators will sit in judgment

00:15.950 --> 00:17.816
Of president
fitzgerald grant iii.

00:17.818 --> 00:19.151
First on the hot seat --

00:19.153 --> 00:21.286
Mellie grant, a senator herself

00:21.288 --> 00:23.288
And the object
of much speculation.

00:23.290 --> 00:24.990
[ camera shutter clicking ]

00:24.992 --> 00:26.492
Do you swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth,

00:26.494 --> 00:27.359
And nothing but the truth,
so help you god?

00:27.361 --> 00:28.861
I do.

00:28.863 --> 00:30.229
Gibson:
It's basic timeline stuff --

00:30.231 --> 00:31.230
Who knew what,
when they knew it.

00:31.232 --> 00:32.698
Just remember, senator,

00:32.700 --> 00:34.900
If there's anything in there
that makes you uncomfortable,

00:34.902 --> 00:37.302
You can always say,
"i don't recall."

00:37.304 --> 00:39.338
-I'm not gonna do that.
-Nor will she have to.

00:39.340 --> 00:41.073
These are
very simple questions.

00:41.075 --> 00:43.509
I'm just saying --
i know what you're saying,
and i appreciate it,

00:43.511 --> 00:45.411
But "i don't recall" --
it's political suicide.

00:45.413 --> 00:47.212
I might as well just say
"i'm guilty."

00:47.214 --> 00:49.982
As long as we are sticking to
this list of questions, though.

00:49.984 --> 00:51.717
We are.

00:51.719 --> 00:53.852
Then we shouldn't have
a problem.

00:53.854 --> 00:56.688
So, ms. Grant, the day ms. Pope
went on national television

00:56.690 --> 00:58.257
And admitted to having
an illicit relationship

00:58.259 --> 00:59.358
With your husband --

00:59.360 --> 01:00.526
Am i to understand

01:00.528 --> 01:02.394
From conversations
you've had with the press

01:02.396 --> 01:03.829
That that was the first
you'd heard of the affair?

01:03.831 --> 01:05.164
Yes.

01:05.166 --> 01:07.166
<i> I wish i could say</i>
<i> i had a feeling,</i>

01:07.168 --> 01:08.667
<i> But the truth is</i>
<i> that i didn't.</i>

01:08.669 --> 01:10.569
Moskowitz:<i> So before ms. Pope</i>
<i> made that announcement,</i>

01:10.571 --> 01:11.570
<i> You had no idea.</i>

01:11.572 --> 01:12.871
<i> No idea at all.</i>

01:12.873 --> 01:16.909
[<i> spectators murmuring</i> ]

01:16.911 --> 01:18.043
Damn it.

01:18.045 --> 01:19.845
What's the matter?

01:19.847 --> 01:22.014
[ cellphone rings ]

01:22.016 --> 01:23.015
You shouldn't be calling.

01:23.017 --> 01:24.283
-It's an ambush.
-What?

01:24.285 --> 01:25.617
Mellie.
They're about to sandbag her.

01:25.619 --> 01:26.952
Who is it?

01:26.954 --> 01:28.153
Liv.
She says it's a trap.

01:30.391 --> 01:32.524
Jeannine locke.

01:32.526 --> 01:34.760
It can't be.

01:34.762 --> 01:36.295
Moskowitz: Ms. Grant,
i'd like to draw your attention

01:36.297 --> 01:39.631
To an affidavit we obtained this
morning from jeannine locke.

01:39.633 --> 01:42.201
Oh, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no. No!

01:42.203 --> 01:44.636
Jeannine locke, you may recall,
is the woman

01:44.638 --> 01:47.639
Your husband claimed to have had
an affair with two years ago.

01:47.641 --> 01:49.575
If you would be so kind

01:49.577 --> 01:50.876
<i> As to read from</i>
<i> the highlighted text there.</i>

01:50.878 --> 01:53.412
This is bad.
This is very, very bad.

01:53.414 --> 01:55.147
If i could request
a recess

01:55.149 --> 01:57.483
To speak with my client,
senator.

01:57.485 --> 01:59.384
You could, counselor,
but we're not going to give it.

01:59.386 --> 02:03.755
The highlighted text, ms. Grant.
What did ms. Locke say?

02:03.757 --> 02:05.791
[ camera shutter clicking ]

02:05.793 --> 02:07.593
"i was about to go on tv

02:07.595 --> 02:10.429
And say i'd never slept with
the president

02:10.431 --> 02:13.465
When the first lady
approached me."

02:13.467 --> 02:14.500
Keep reading.

02:19.006 --> 02:20.739
"mrs. Grant said

02:20.741 --> 02:23.642
That she knew i wasn't the woman
sleeping with her husband,

02:23.644 --> 02:25.911
But if i lied
and said that i was,

02:25.913 --> 02:28.580
She would pay me $2 million.

02:28.582 --> 02:31.316
She said my life would be ruined
regardless of what i said,

02:31.318 --> 02:32.784
So i might as well
profit from it,

02:32.786 --> 02:34.319
So that's what i did."

02:34.321 --> 02:36.121
In other words,
you lied to us.

02:36.123 --> 02:38.423
<i> You knew about your husband's</i>
<i> affair with olivia</i>

02:38.425 --> 02:41.593
<i> Long before ms. Pope confessed</i>
<i> to it on national television,</i>

02:41.595 --> 02:43.629
<i> And because it was</i>
<i> so politically dangerous,</i>

02:43.631 --> 02:46.431
You helped ms. Pope
and your husband cover it up.

02:46.433 --> 02:47.933
Yes or no, ms. Grant?

02:49.603 --> 02:50.936
I don't recall.

02:50.938 --> 02:52.070
I'm sorry?

02:56.043 --> 02:57.809
I don't recall.

02:57.811 --> 03:00.712
We see you, grant family,

03:00.714 --> 03:04.383
Bonded by sin to olivia pope
and her criminal minions.

03:04.385 --> 03:07.619
The scales have finally fallen
from our eyes,

03:07.621 --> 03:11.123
And for that, dear members of
the senate judiciary committee,

03:11.125 --> 03:21.533
We as lovers of liberty,
salute you.

03:21.535 --> 03:22.834
Senator grant all but admitted

03:22.836 --> 03:24.503
To not only having
prior knowledge

03:24.505 --> 03:26.338
Of her husband's affair
with olivia pope --

03:26.340 --> 03:28.540
...Allegedly paying
former white house staffer
jeannine locke

03:28.542 --> 03:30.909
To lie about having an affair
with the president.

03:30.911 --> 03:31.977
Why didn't anyone warn me

03:31.979 --> 03:33.245
About the jeannine locke
situation?

03:33.247 --> 03:35.914
We're changing strategy --
full 180.

03:35.916 --> 03:37.549
You no longer testify,
mr. President,

03:37.551 --> 03:39.651
Or cooperate in any way
with the investigation.

03:39.653 --> 03:42.254
We invoke
executive privilege?
Yes.

03:42.256 --> 03:43.355
We say
congress can't force you,

03:43.357 --> 03:44.990
Call them out
on the investigation,

03:44.992 --> 03:47.259
Say it's no more justified
than a salem witch hunt.

03:47.261 --> 03:48.927
That might save<i> me</i>
from having to testify,

03:48.929 --> 03:50.062
But what about<i> olivia?</i>

03:52.166 --> 03:54.132
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

03:55.869 --> 03:57.436
[ door closes ]

03:57.438 --> 03:59.538
-We think we have a way out.
-Is that why you called?

03:59.540 --> 04:01.607
We can't discuss this.
-It's not about jeannine.

04:01.609 --> 04:03.208
We shouldn't even
be saying her name.
If you just listen --

04:03.210 --> 04:05.577
I can't listen!
We can't even discuss --

04:05.579 --> 04:07.613
For the -- [ sighs ]

04:07.615 --> 04:09.781
We didn't call you here to talk
about the investigation.

04:09.783 --> 04:11.016
We called you here
to discuss a wedding.

04:12.453 --> 04:14.620
<i> Our</i> wedding.

04:14.622 --> 04:16.555
It's the only way
out of this,

04:16.557 --> 04:18.223
The only way to keep you
from having to testify.

04:18.225 --> 04:21.360
You two
are getting married.

04:21.362 --> 04:23.895
The day of reckoning is upon us.

04:23.897 --> 04:25.731
Tell me you are here
with good news.

04:25.733 --> 04:27.199
I've set up
all your bank accounts,

04:27.201 --> 04:28.433
Passport i.D.,
all ready to go.

04:28.435 --> 04:30.636
Ahh.

04:30.638 --> 04:33.105
That's a good start.
You've done well, elise.

04:33.107 --> 04:36.074
We just have
one more piece of business.

04:36.076 --> 04:38.277
Your escape plan.
Mm.

04:41.248 --> 04:43.282
You need to get in
right there.

04:43.284 --> 04:44.716
The laundry hamper.

04:44.718 --> 04:47.052
Or you can wait 10 years
while i dig you a tunnel.

04:51.258 --> 04:53.191
I'm talking to you,
mr. President.

04:54.061 --> 04:56.328
Today begins a new chapter.

04:56.330 --> 04:59.264
Our founding fathers
called it impeachment.

04:59.266 --> 05:01.266
I call it judgment day,

05:01.268 --> 05:03.602
The day
when our sins sprout legs

05:03.604 --> 05:05.804
And chase us to our graves.

05:05.806 --> 05:08.307
Ask not for whom the bell tolls,
mr. President.

05:08.309 --> 05:12.110
The laundry truck left
two hours ago.

05:12.112 --> 05:13.745
Aah!

05:13.747 --> 05:14.680
[ bell dings ]

05:14.682 --> 05:16.148
It tolls for thee.

05:24.792 --> 05:26.525
Cyrus: If you're married,
you can claim spousal privilege.

05:26.527 --> 05:28.260
If you can claim spousal
privilege, you don't
have to testify.

05:28.262 --> 05:30.829
He's not --
you're not even divorced!

05:30.831 --> 05:32.964
Terms have been accepted.

05:32.966 --> 05:34.366
Papers have been drawn.

05:34.368 --> 05:35.634
Mellie is as eager to sign
as i am.

05:35.636 --> 05:38.537
Have you stopped to consider
how insane this idea is?

05:38.539 --> 05:40.672
A shotgun wedding on the heels
of a quickie divorce?

05:40.674 --> 05:42.374
You may as well turn
the oval office

05:42.376 --> 05:44.176
Into a drive-through
wedding chapel.

05:44.178 --> 05:46.545
We're talking about survival.
We can fix the optics later.

05:46.547 --> 05:48.280
I married a whore.

05:48.282 --> 05:50.282
You landed michael and me

05:50.284 --> 05:52.984
On the cover of<i> out and proud</i>
magazine twice in one year.

05:52.986 --> 05:56.455
Jeannine locke
won't take us down.

05:56.457 --> 05:58.056
Trust me.

05:58.058 --> 05:59.491
You go
before that committee,

05:59.493 --> 06:01.226
And jeannine locke
is the tip of the iceberg.

06:01.228 --> 06:02.494
They sandbagged mellie.

06:02.496 --> 06:04.396
You don't think
they'll do the same to you?

06:04.398 --> 06:06.131
With defiance?

06:06.133 --> 06:08.033
Or remington? Or --
enough, cy.

06:08.035 --> 06:10.802
Okay.

06:12.172 --> 06:13.638
We'll find another way.

06:15.542 --> 06:17.809
Oh, my --

06:17.811 --> 06:19.878
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

06:19.880 --> 06:21.880
Any time an inmate
needs medical care,

06:21.882 --> 06:23.482
We call
the emergency contact.

06:23.484 --> 06:25.016
In this case,
he didn't have one.

06:25.018 --> 06:26.885
Okay, so why call me?

06:26.887 --> 06:28.887
You're one of only two visitors
mr. Pope has had

06:28.889 --> 06:29.988
Since he was incarcerated.

06:29.990 --> 06:31.556
You were actually
our second call.

06:31.558 --> 06:34.226
Do you an...Elise martin?

06:36.029 --> 06:37.129
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

06:39.600 --> 06:41.366
You looking for this?

06:41.368 --> 06:44.069
Yes.
It's my favorite.

06:46.940 --> 06:48.774
Why have you been visiting rowan
in prison?

06:48.776 --> 06:51.676
I didn't --

06:51.678 --> 06:53.245
Don't lie to me.

06:53.247 --> 06:55.514
He's, um...

06:57.718 --> 06:58.950
Rowan's why i'm here --

06:58.952 --> 07:01.019
In the u.S., in d.C.

07:01.021 --> 07:04.189
You're running
lazarus one?

07:04.191 --> 07:06.591
No, i was hired by the people
running lazarus one,

07:06.593 --> 07:08.593
And they're taking out
their enemies.

07:08.595 --> 07:09.761
You're here to free him.

07:09.763 --> 07:10.862
I'm here to kill him.

07:10.864 --> 07:12.898
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

07:12.900 --> 07:14.566
You want me
to make it quick?

07:14.568 --> 07:15.634
Not particularly.

07:17.704 --> 07:19.438
Who are you working for?
Who's looking to replace him?

07:19.440 --> 07:20.472
I don't know.

07:20.474 --> 07:22.307
Does it really matter?

07:22.309 --> 07:25.043
The world will be a better place
without rowan in it.

07:28.115 --> 07:29.614
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

07:29.616 --> 07:31.450
Good morning.

07:31.452 --> 07:34.286
And what a beautiful morning
it is in our nation's capital.

07:34.288 --> 07:37.122
Today, freedom shall ring
loud and clear

07:37.124 --> 07:39.724
As olivia pope's
band of lawbreakers

07:39.726 --> 07:43.662
Must explain their involvement
in the jeannine locke cover-up.

07:43.664 --> 07:45.664
This should be good.

07:45.666 --> 07:47.766
Olivia: No one lies.
No one perjures themselves.

07:47.768 --> 07:49.801
No one goes to jail.
Those are the rules.

07:49.803 --> 07:51.403
Is that clear?
Crystal.

07:51.405 --> 07:52.637
Abby?

07:52.639 --> 07:54.105
I got a subpoena.

07:54.107 --> 07:55.640
Who's he?
He's the new guy.

07:55.642 --> 07:56.975
It's marcus.

07:56.977 --> 07:59.411
I'm waist-deep in this.
So where are we?

07:59.413 --> 08:00.445
Well, we're trying
to avoid perjury.

08:00.447 --> 08:02.180
Or worse.

08:02.182 --> 08:04.149
Who came up with the plan
to frame jeannine locke?

08:04.151 --> 08:07.319
[ camera shutter clicking ]

08:07.321 --> 08:09.454
Listen to the questions
very carefully.

08:09.456 --> 08:10.989
Literally.

08:10.991 --> 08:13.191
Do you know
who came up with the plan?

08:13.193 --> 08:14.693
I think it was --
don't think.

08:14.695 --> 08:16.795
Don't guess.
Don't speculate.

08:16.797 --> 08:18.330
Answer the question.

08:18.332 --> 08:19.598
Do you know?

08:19.600 --> 08:20.932
I don't know.

08:20.934 --> 08:22.334
Mr. Muñoz?

08:22.336 --> 08:23.435
Uh, i don't know.

08:23.437 --> 08:24.636
Ms. Perkins?

08:24.638 --> 08:26.338
No idea.

08:26.340 --> 08:28.773
If they aren't satisfied
with your answers,
which they won't be,

08:28.775 --> 08:30.775
They'll start asking
you questions about
specific evidence

08:30.777 --> 08:33.478
In order to force you
into perjuring yourselves.

08:33.480 --> 08:35.580
What else do they have
that links us to jeannine locke?

08:37.451 --> 08:38.717
The video.

08:40.888 --> 08:43.822
<i> I think that governor grant</i>
<i> has the election in the bag.</i>

08:43.824 --> 08:48.627
<i> Most importantly,</i>
<i> he is freakin' hot.</i>

08:48.629 --> 08:49.961
If they ask
about the video --

08:49.963 --> 08:51.029
Then they know we leaked it.

08:51.031 --> 08:52.631
-Did you leak it?
-Of course we leaked it.

08:52.633 --> 08:53.899
You, personally,
leaked the video?

08:53.901 --> 08:55.133
Well, not<i> personally.</i>

08:55.135 --> 08:57.168
That's the question.

08:57.170 --> 09:00.605
Did<i> you</i> leak a video
of ms. Locke?

09:01.408 --> 09:03.308
Did you?

09:03.310 --> 09:04.643
No, i did not.

09:04.645 --> 09:06.244
Ms. Perkins, mr. Muñoz?

09:06.246 --> 09:07.245
I did not.

09:07.247 --> 09:08.380
What she said.

09:08.382 --> 09:10.215
Okay, ms. Whelan,

09:10.217 --> 09:13.218
If it wasn't you
or mr. Muñoz or ms. Perkins,

09:13.220 --> 09:15.587
Who did leak the video
of ms. Locke?

09:15.589 --> 09:17.822
And let me remind you
that you are under oath.

09:20.761 --> 09:22.827
[ sighs ]

09:22.829 --> 09:24.029
It was harrison.

09:24.031 --> 09:25.063
What?

09:25.065 --> 09:26.331
And he's dead.
That's great.

09:27.834 --> 09:29.568
Okay, maybe not great,

09:29.570 --> 09:31.369
But you can't send a dead guy
to jail, right?

09:31.371 --> 09:33.772
It's the truth.
I-it was actually him.

09:33.774 --> 09:34.673
Yeah, we wouldn't be
committing perjury.

09:34.675 --> 09:36.174
That's disgusting.

09:36.176 --> 09:37.175
Liv, is it?

09:38.779 --> 09:40.579
Together: Harrison wright.

09:42.549 --> 09:44.449
You're saying
the person who's responsible

09:44.451 --> 09:46.418
For leaking the video
that was used to frame ms. Locke

09:46.420 --> 09:49.521
Just happens
to no longer be with us?

09:49.523 --> 09:51.890
[ spectators murmuring ]

09:51.892 --> 09:53.191
[ gavel bangs ]

09:53.193 --> 09:54.793
We're all going to hell.

09:57.230 --> 09:59.598
It might not have been pretty,
but it got the job done.

09:59.600 --> 10:01.533
Now it's up to me.

10:01.535 --> 10:03.101
Figured out
what you're gonna say?

10:03.103 --> 10:04.769
You testify in two days.

10:04.771 --> 10:06.771
I'm still weighing
my options.

10:06.773 --> 10:07.973
[ telephone rings ]

10:07.975 --> 10:08.974
Pope and associates.

10:08.976 --> 10:10.575
Who's calling?

10:10.577 --> 10:12.544
It's a nurse for you.

10:15.449 --> 10:17.082
Olivia pope.

10:17.084 --> 10:18.483
One moment, please.

10:18.485 --> 10:20.785
[ monitor beeping ]
olivia.

10:20.787 --> 10:23.221
Olivia, i-i need your help.
I've been attacked.

10:23.223 --> 10:24.623
My life is in danger and --

10:24.625 --> 10:25.991
[ receiver clicks, dial tone ]

10:25.993 --> 10:27.125
Oli-olivia?

10:29.496 --> 10:30.161
Who was that?

10:33.000 --> 10:34.532
No one.

10:40.841 --> 10:42.307
Mr. Rosen.

10:42.309 --> 10:44.275
Madam vice president.
Did we have an appointment?

10:44.277 --> 10:45.243
No.

10:45.245 --> 10:46.745
Oh.

10:46.747 --> 10:48.580
Is this a bad time?

10:48.582 --> 10:50.015
It is, isn't it?
A bad time?

10:50.017 --> 10:51.616
I can tell
by the look on your face.

10:51.618 --> 10:54.185
It's just
that something's come up,

10:54.187 --> 10:55.587
Kind of
spur-of-the-moment.

10:55.589 --> 10:57.255
Hold my calls.
There.

10:57.257 --> 10:58.623
It is no longer
a bad time.

10:58.625 --> 11:00.025
Please.

11:01.328 --> 11:03.161
Now...

11:03.163 --> 11:06.264
What can i do for you?

11:06.266 --> 11:07.632
[ laughs loudly ]

11:07.634 --> 11:09.834
[ laughing ] s-sorry.

11:09.836 --> 11:11.169
Ah.

11:13.340 --> 11:17.042
I'm sorry.
Anyway, so, why i'm here.

11:17.044 --> 11:18.443
Right.

11:18.445 --> 11:21.146
Obviously, i can rely
on your discretion.

11:21.148 --> 11:22.714
You can.

11:22.716 --> 11:23.948
Of course i can.

11:23.950 --> 11:25.850
You're the attorney general
of the united states.

11:25.852 --> 11:27.786
You're probably the most
discrete person in the country.

11:27.788 --> 11:28.953
One of them.

11:30.223 --> 11:31.956
All right, then.

11:31.958 --> 11:33.992
Deep breath.
Here it goes.

11:33.994 --> 11:36.294
I would like your opinion
on whether there are

11:36.296 --> 11:38.630
Any legal obstacles
to resignation.

11:38.632 --> 11:41.666
To your resignation?

11:41.668 --> 11:43.068
As in, quit your job?

11:43.070 --> 11:45.303
Well...

11:45.305 --> 11:49.307
It sounds funny that way,
but...Yes.

11:49.309 --> 11:51.309
I want to quit my job

11:51.311 --> 11:53.144
As vice president
of the united states.

11:56.483 --> 11:59.818
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

11:59.820 --> 12:01.686
Will you sit down?

12:01.688 --> 12:03.421
I'm in the president's bedroom.
It's weird.

12:03.423 --> 12:05.056
Don't you feel weird?

12:05.058 --> 12:06.891
Eleanor roosevelt
had sex in here.

12:06.893 --> 12:09.394
Abby.
No, i mean, jackie o.,
lady bird, pat nixon.

12:09.396 --> 12:11.262
I mean, can you imagine
being first lady,

12:11.264 --> 12:13.431
Sleeping in this room,
living life here,
part of history?

12:13.433 --> 12:15.233
No privacy, no sense of
personal space, no --

12:15.235 --> 12:16.935
If i marry fitz,
i won't have to testify.

12:16.937 --> 12:19.070
What? Wait.
Is that an option?

12:19.072 --> 12:21.706
Cyrus tried to handle me
into it.

12:21.708 --> 12:24.375
But yeah, it's an option,
i guess.

12:24.377 --> 12:26.177
Well, that's good,
right?

12:28.782 --> 12:32.851
[ sighs ]

12:32.853 --> 12:35.620
If i go before that committee
and testify,

12:35.622 --> 12:37.255
I'm going to lie.

12:37.257 --> 12:39.457
Okay, it's the senate
judiciary committee, liv.

12:39.459 --> 12:40.859
You wouldn't do that.
Abby.

12:40.861 --> 12:43.294
Liv.
You can't do that.

12:43.296 --> 12:45.296
I know you mean it,

12:45.298 --> 12:47.866
But i'm telling you as a lawyer,
you can't.

12:47.868 --> 12:49.934
You can't perjure yourself.

12:49.936 --> 12:51.903
This isn't traffic court.
It's the u.S. Government.

12:51.905 --> 12:54.405
I'm going to lie.
I'm going to perjure myself

12:54.407 --> 12:57.041
Because otherwise,
fitz will be impeached.

12:57.043 --> 12:59.344
And i love him too much
to let that happen.

13:01.314 --> 13:02.480
So i need a way out.

13:02.482 --> 13:03.882
So marry him.

13:03.884 --> 13:05.216
[ sighs ]
that's your way out.

13:05.218 --> 13:07.118
You love him.
You wouldn't have to testify.

13:07.120 --> 13:09.254
We're not ready
to get married.

13:09.256 --> 13:12.490
It'd just be a last-minute
"get out of jail free" card.

13:12.492 --> 13:13.992
I don't want that for us.

13:13.994 --> 13:17.095
And pretending that i do
is just another lie.

13:17.097 --> 13:21.666
If you take the stand,
you could end up going to jail.

13:21.668 --> 13:24.669
And if i get married?

13:27.841 --> 13:30.475
What in the hell
do you think this is?

13:33.180 --> 13:34.612
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

13:34.614 --> 13:37.148
These senators aren't going home
without bagging a trophy.

13:37.150 --> 13:38.349
We need to do something.

13:38.351 --> 13:39.984
She only told us
not to lie.

13:39.986 --> 13:42.120
She didn't tell us
we couldn't do other things.

13:42.122 --> 13:44.355
Huck.

13:44.357 --> 13:46.925
I didn't say kill.
You really need to let that go.

13:46.927 --> 13:48.793
[ cellphone rings ]
[ sighs ]

13:48.795 --> 13:49.894
Hello?

13:53.166 --> 13:54.666
Who is it?

13:54.668 --> 13:55.767
It's just charlie.

13:58.038 --> 14:00.138
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

14:00.140 --> 14:01.539
Thank you for coming.

14:01.541 --> 14:04.209
I am not lifting a finger
for you.

14:04.211 --> 14:05.610
You just want to
get out of here,

14:05.612 --> 14:07.011
And i'm not
going to help you do it.

14:09.049 --> 14:10.014
Sir.

14:11.985 --> 14:14.185
Are we done?

14:17.390 --> 14:19.657
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

14:19.659 --> 14:22.126
[ aretha franklin's
"ain't no way" plays ]

14:44.184 --> 14:46.050
♪ ain't no way ♪

14:49.389 --> 14:51.823
♪ for me to love you ♪
[ chuckles ]

14:51.825 --> 14:52.757
What is all this?

14:52.759 --> 14:55.226
This is my do-over.

14:55.228 --> 14:57.428
Your what?
I get it, liv.

14:57.430 --> 14:59.430
Why you weren't so crazy
about the whole marriage idea.

14:59.432 --> 15:02.834
In the oval,
listening to cyrus rattle on

15:02.836 --> 15:05.570
About subpoenas
and privilege and optics.

15:05.572 --> 15:08.239
It was all so...
Impersonal.

15:08.241 --> 15:09.841
As if the two of us
getting married

15:09.843 --> 15:11.342
Was just
some kind of transaction.

15:11.344 --> 15:12.677
It felt wrong.

15:12.679 --> 15:15.713
And so...

15:15.715 --> 15:17.181
I want another shot.

15:17.183 --> 15:19.517
You and i
deserve another shot.

15:19.519 --> 15:22.887
A do-over.

15:22.889 --> 15:26.024
To make this feel right.

15:26.026 --> 15:27.692
Fitz.

15:27.694 --> 15:29.594
♪ i know that a woman's duty ♪

15:29.596 --> 15:30.695
Olivia pope.

15:30.697 --> 15:32.096
Fitz, please get up.

15:32.098 --> 15:34.065
♪ is to help and love a man ♪

15:34.067 --> 15:35.366
Please get up.

15:35.368 --> 15:36.868
Liv.

15:36.870 --> 15:39.370
♪ and that's the way ♪

15:39.372 --> 15:41.706
♪ it was planned ♪
i'm sorry.

15:41.708 --> 15:43.241
What do you mean?
Olivia!

15:43.243 --> 15:46.277
♪ ooh, ooh ♪

15:46.279 --> 15:47.946
I thought
this was what you wanted.

15:47.948 --> 15:49.948
This is<i> not</i>
what i wanted.

15:49.950 --> 15:52.050
Well, what do you want?

15:52.052 --> 15:53.584
Not this.

15:53.586 --> 15:57.088
Not some fake
storybook romance,

15:57.090 --> 15:59.757
Some teenage girl's
fantasy.

15:59.759 --> 16:01.492
And do you think
this is what<i> i</i> want?

16:01.494 --> 16:02.794
Do you have any idea --

16:02.796 --> 16:04.829
I should be downstairs
in the sit room

16:04.831 --> 16:06.731
Discussing any number
of pressing concerns

16:06.733 --> 16:08.132
With my generals,

16:08.134 --> 16:12.136
Like the war on terror
or those bombings in bolivia.

16:12.138 --> 16:15.173
Instead,
i'm asking charlotte

16:15.175 --> 16:17.742
To scour every presidential
library in the country

16:17.744 --> 16:20.011
For rare and unique
engagement rings.

16:20.013 --> 16:22.146
This one
belonged to betsy ross.

16:22.148 --> 16:23.648
You know
how embarrassing that was?

16:23.650 --> 16:25.316
How awkward i felt

16:25.318 --> 16:27.585
Asking my valets to scatter
rose petals everywhere?

16:27.587 --> 16:29.287
Telling them to light
all these damn candles?

16:29.289 --> 16:31.622
Can you honestly stand there
and tell me

16:31.624 --> 16:34.659
That you think that
i actually wanted to do this?

16:34.661 --> 16:36.327
Nobody wants to do this!

16:36.329 --> 16:38.429
No man
ever wants to do this.

16:38.431 --> 16:40.531
Of course no man
ever wants to do this.

16:40.533 --> 16:41.699
So why did you do it?

16:41.701 --> 16:43.334
Because i love you.

16:43.336 --> 16:45.570
Because
you are what i want.

16:48.608 --> 16:51.776
But obviously,
you don't feel the same.

16:51.778 --> 16:56.781
♪ stop tryin' to be
someone you're not ♪

16:56.783 --> 16:58.783
Some fantasy, right?

16:58.785 --> 17:00.718
♪ ooh ♪

17:00.720 --> 17:02.687
We're not ready.

17:02.689 --> 17:04.489
<i> You're</i> not ready.

17:04.491 --> 17:06.791
And you know what i think?

17:06.793 --> 17:09.227
You never will be.

17:09.229 --> 17:10.828
That's not fair.

17:10.830 --> 17:13.297
♪ and if you need me ♪

17:13.299 --> 17:15.166
Then answer the question,
olivia.

17:15.168 --> 17:19.537
♪ like you say,
say-ay you do ♪

17:19.539 --> 17:22.407
♪ oh, then, please, please ♪
what is it that you want?

17:22.409 --> 17:27.245
♪ please, don't you know
that i need you? ♪

17:27.247 --> 17:29.313
That's what i thought.

17:29.315 --> 17:32.250
♪ oh, it ain't no way ♪

17:32.252 --> 17:34.819
♪ ooh, ooh ♪

17:34.821 --> 17:36.821
♪ i tell you
that it ain't no way ♪

17:36.823 --> 17:39.724
♪ it ain't no way,
it ain't no way, baby ♪

17:43.163 --> 17:47.098
[ cellphone rings ]

17:47.100 --> 17:48.099
Liv.

17:48.101 --> 17:49.567
Hey.
Hey.

17:49.569 --> 17:51.102
Where are you?
At home.

17:51.104 --> 17:52.537
Are you okay?
You sound --

17:52.539 --> 17:54.539
I can be a married person,
right?

17:54.541 --> 17:56.541
What?

17:56.543 --> 17:59.577
You think
i'd be okay being married?

17:59.579 --> 18:00.745
That i could do it?

18:00.747 --> 18:02.847
Because i think
i might have to get married.

18:02.849 --> 18:04.682
To him?
Are you calling to --

18:04.684 --> 18:06.050
[ chuckles ]

18:06.052 --> 18:07.618
Liv, i have to go.

18:07.620 --> 18:10.254
I need to know what to do.
You're who i talk to.

18:10.256 --> 18:11.923
Mm-hmm. About whether or not
to marry him.

18:11.925 --> 18:13.257
I know. I'm sorry.
I just --

18:13.259 --> 18:16.027
I'm gonna hang up
the phone now, liv.

18:18.264 --> 18:20.998
[ knock on door ]

18:26.106 --> 18:28.272
We just got word
from moskowitz's office.

18:28.274 --> 18:30.908
You're their first witness
up friday morning.

18:30.910 --> 18:32.410
You could've called
to tell me that.

18:32.412 --> 18:33.945
I wanted to make sure
you were okay.

18:33.947 --> 18:37.215
Quinn: I saw abby earlier.
So, are you okay?

18:37.217 --> 18:38.749
I'm fine.

18:38.751 --> 18:39.884
Are you gonna testify
tomorrow?

18:39.886 --> 18:40.952
I don't know.

18:40.954 --> 18:42.220
Are you going to
get married?

18:44.624 --> 18:45.823
I don't know.

18:45.825 --> 18:46.891
Do you want
to get married?

18:46.893 --> 18:47.992
Quinn.

18:47.994 --> 18:50.061
Sorry.

18:54.634 --> 18:57.869
If you don't have a solution,
i'd like to be alone.

18:59.806 --> 19:01.205
I might.

19:02.308 --> 19:04.575
Have a solution.

19:06.980 --> 19:09.280
You're going around my back,
working my team?

19:09.282 --> 19:11.415
You left me no choice.
You were avoiding my calls.

19:11.417 --> 19:13.584
You look fine.

19:13.586 --> 19:14.685
I am fine.

19:14.687 --> 19:15.820
So why are you still
in the infirmary?

19:15.822 --> 19:18.623
My heart.
It's behaving erratically.

19:18.625 --> 19:20.758
[ monitor beeping ]

19:20.760 --> 19:22.160
Looks fine to me.

19:22.162 --> 19:25.129
[ monitor beeping quickly ]

19:25.131 --> 19:27.365
[ beeping slows ]

19:27.367 --> 19:30.201
I've been faking arrhythmias
for the last 12 hours.

19:30.203 --> 19:31.702
So you can see visitors?

19:31.704 --> 19:34.438
So i don't return to my cell
so i am not killed.

19:34.440 --> 19:35.806
I think it's time

19:35.808 --> 19:37.675
The doctors learn about
your little parlor trick.

19:37.677 --> 19:40.444
Olivia, if i go back to my cell,
i will not come out alive.

19:40.446 --> 19:41.779
You killed a guard.

19:41.781 --> 19:43.447
You're worried the other guards
will retaliate.

19:43.449 --> 19:45.216
The threat
is far greater than that.

19:45.218 --> 19:46.984
Whoever's behind this
will try again and again,

19:46.986 --> 19:48.619
As many times
as necessary.

19:48.621 --> 19:51.556
They will kill me.
You have to get me out of here.

19:57.630 --> 19:59.497
Goodbye, dad.

19:59.499 --> 20:01.065
I'm not asking for --

20:01.067 --> 20:03.000
I'm offering you
something in return,

20:03.002 --> 20:05.570
Something of equal value
to you.

20:05.572 --> 20:07.705
The committee --

20:07.707 --> 20:09.373
I can make it
so it all goes away.

20:09.375 --> 20:11.842
The hearings, the impeachment --
all of it.

20:11.844 --> 20:13.177
Those b613 files,

20:13.179 --> 20:14.679
The ones you thought
were all destroyed

20:14.681 --> 20:15.746
Are all right here.

20:15.748 --> 20:16.881
I know everything

20:16.883 --> 20:18.883
About every last member
of that committee.

20:18.885 --> 20:20.551
Get me out of this prison,

20:20.553 --> 20:22.587
And i'll get you
out of this mess.

20:31.931 --> 20:34.065
[ sighs ]

20:43.042 --> 20:44.575
I can sign fitz's signature
in my sleep.

20:44.577 --> 20:45.743
I can do it perfectly.

20:45.745 --> 20:47.144
I've been doing it
since he was governor.

20:59.559 --> 21:02.126
Thank you for coming.
I have a proposition.

21:02.128 --> 21:03.227
You mentioned that.

21:03.229 --> 21:04.295
A way out.

21:04.297 --> 21:06.530
A way out of what,
exactly?

21:06.532 --> 21:07.932
This mess that we're in.

21:07.934 --> 21:09.934
I'm already out, liv.
I am out.

21:09.936 --> 21:11.602
I am down.
I am down here.

21:11.604 --> 21:12.603
You see me.

21:12.605 --> 21:14.639
Did you see
what happened yesterday?

21:14.641 --> 21:18.909
Those flesh-eating cannibals.
I am out of the hearings.

21:18.911 --> 21:20.478
I am out
of the committee.

21:20.480 --> 21:23.281
I am probably out of the senate,
which means i am out of a job.

21:23.283 --> 21:25.483
I am out of a career.
I am out of my house.

21:25.485 --> 21:27.485
I am out of my marriage,
thanks to you.

21:27.487 --> 21:29.053
I am out!

21:30.590 --> 21:32.156
It can get worse.

21:32.158 --> 21:34.058
It cannot get worse.

21:34.060 --> 21:35.293
Not for me.

21:35.295 --> 21:37.228
If i testify
before that committee,

21:37.230 --> 21:38.262
It<i> will</i> get worse.

21:38.264 --> 21:40.264
You're threatening me?

21:40.266 --> 21:42.066
I'm not threatening you.

21:42.068 --> 21:44.168
I'm telling you the truth.

21:44.170 --> 21:47.605
What does that committee
really have?

21:47.607 --> 21:51.342
Not west angola, not defiance,
not 100 other things.

21:51.344 --> 21:53.611
They have a statement
from jeannine locke.

21:53.613 --> 21:54.578
That's it.

21:57.850 --> 22:00.785
I know it was bad for you
yesterday,

22:00.787 --> 22:05.289
But you can survive that story
because if i don't testify,

22:05.291 --> 22:07.158
That story dies
and these hearings end

22:07.160 --> 22:09.260
And jeannine locke
becomes the answer

22:09.262 --> 22:11.696
To a trivia question
no one ever gets right.

22:11.698 --> 22:14.298
But if i testify,
everything changes.

22:14.300 --> 22:17.134
If i testify, they will ask me
about everything

22:17.136 --> 22:19.670
And i will have to answer
and we will all go down.

22:19.672 --> 22:21.439
I despise you.

22:24.510 --> 22:28.846
There's a prisoner
in virginia.

22:28.848 --> 22:30.715
If you can secure
his release,

22:30.717 --> 22:34.719
And i know that you can,
and i know how you can do that,

22:34.721 --> 22:37.988
He will make
these proceedings go away --

22:37.990 --> 22:39.557
No violence,
no one gets hurt.

22:39.559 --> 22:42.326
All of this
will just disappear.

22:42.328 --> 22:44.662
You will be out of this maze
and back into your life.

22:44.664 --> 22:47.131
You know what i can do, mellie.
You know what i'm capable of.

22:47.133 --> 22:49.367
I'm telling you --
this is our way out.

22:49.369 --> 22:50.267
Your way out.

22:53.473 --> 22:55.873
[ sighs ]

22:57.477 --> 22:59.176
Who is he?

22:59.178 --> 23:00.745
It doesn't matter.

23:02.682 --> 23:03.614
Who is he?

23:13.593 --> 23:15.059
His name is --

23:15.061 --> 23:18.863
I know his name.
Damascus bainbridge.

23:18.865 --> 23:21.899
What the hell is going on?
How did he get to you?

23:21.901 --> 23:23.434
Damascus bainbridge --

23:23.436 --> 23:24.935
That is his name.

23:24.937 --> 23:26.570
That is not his name.
Don't.

23:26.572 --> 23:28.539
Don't do this, olivia.

23:28.541 --> 23:30.641
His name is eli pope.

23:32.745 --> 23:34.912
What?

23:34.914 --> 23:37.014
His name is eli pope.

23:37.016 --> 23:39.316
He's my father.

23:51.030 --> 23:53.764
I don't understand.

23:55.435 --> 23:59.036
He came to me.
Damascus bainbridge.

23:59.038 --> 24:01.205
He said he was a donor,

24:01.207 --> 24:03.374
But he wanted information
on those jurors.

24:03.376 --> 24:05.276
He killed
those 17 federal jurors.

24:05.278 --> 24:06.544
Did you know that?

24:06.546 --> 24:09.113
This is your father?
Who is he?

24:09.115 --> 24:10.481
What does he do?

24:14.320 --> 24:17.288
My father ran
a secret intelligence agency

24:17.290 --> 24:19.623
Within
the united states government.

24:19.625 --> 24:22.259
What kind of intelligence agency
kills jurors?

24:22.261 --> 24:24.829
It was not a normal
intelligence agency.

24:28.468 --> 24:32.303
Fitz never told you
that this man came to me?

24:32.305 --> 24:35.172
No.

24:35.174 --> 24:39.143
Then why did you think
he threw me out?

24:48.855 --> 24:52.022
I didn't know.

25:04.837 --> 25:06.437
Your father
is a murderer.

25:06.439 --> 25:10.274
He slaughtered
innocent people,

25:10.276 --> 25:13.110
And you want me
to release him from jail.

25:13.112 --> 25:15.312
Just like that.

25:15.314 --> 25:17.648
Without even knowing
what i was doing.

25:17.650 --> 25:20.518
So that you and fitz can live
happily upstairs together

25:20.520 --> 25:22.386
For another couple
of years?

25:22.388 --> 25:25.956
How sick is that?
How sick are<i> you?</i>

25:25.958 --> 25:30.227
But i guess the apple doesn't
fall far from the tree, does it?

25:30.229 --> 25:34.331
Your daddy wasn't<i> my</i> way out.
He was<i> yours.</i>

25:34.333 --> 25:36.634
Probably like he's always been
your whole life --

25:36.636 --> 25:38.335
Mowing people down

25:38.337 --> 25:41.639
To clear a path
for his golden child.

25:41.641 --> 25:43.407
[ chuckles ]

25:43.409 --> 25:46.243
Who else
has he done this to?

25:46.245 --> 25:49.813
Who else has he hurt?
Do you even know?

25:53.419 --> 25:56.287
[ scoffs ]

25:59.091 --> 26:01.125
He killed your son.

26:08.167 --> 26:10.334
My father
killed your son.

26:18.711 --> 26:21.178
[ hyperventilating ]

26:42.568 --> 26:44.602
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

27:02.655 --> 27:04.688
Let me see the ring.

27:27.480 --> 27:29.079
Who did you say
it belonged to?

27:29.081 --> 27:30.914
Betsy ross.

27:53.439 --> 27:55.339
Okay.

27:57.443 --> 27:59.276
Okay.

28:03.215 --> 28:06.717
No wedding dress, no flowers,
and no vows.

28:06.719 --> 28:09.219
And i'm keeping my name.

28:09.221 --> 28:11.188
Good.

28:11.190 --> 28:12.823
'cause i'm only marrying you
for your money.

28:12.825 --> 28:15.192
[ chuckles ]

28:34.246 --> 28:36.513
[ cellphone rings ]
[ sighs ] what?

28:36.515 --> 28:38.415
I'm gonna do it.

28:40.186 --> 28:42.286
Okay.
Well, good for you.

28:46.192 --> 28:50.260
I didn't want you to hear
on tv or something.

28:51.664 --> 28:53.797
Whatever.

28:56.368 --> 28:57.568
Jake,
i need you to be --

28:57.570 --> 28:58.769
Stop it. Don't...

28:58.771 --> 29:01.338
You need me for anything.

29:01.340 --> 29:04.274
Don't you ask me
for anything.

29:04.276 --> 29:05.909
That's<i> his</i> job.

29:05.911 --> 29:07.611
Please.

29:07.613 --> 29:10.514
Congratulations.

29:13.586 --> 29:15.719
Elise.

29:15.721 --> 29:17.788
I'm coming with you.

29:17.790 --> 29:19.456
What's the plan?

29:21.260 --> 29:23.927
Union station,
3:00 tomorrow.

29:23.929 --> 29:26.130
3:00 tomorrow.

29:26.132 --> 29:27.998
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

29:29.268 --> 29:31.969
Our assets will be divided
50/50,

29:31.971 --> 29:33.403
Aside from the house
in santa barbara.

29:33.405 --> 29:34.972
I figured
you'd still wanted that,

29:34.974 --> 29:36.306
And i'm not gonna
fight you for it.

29:36.308 --> 29:37.541
How generous of you.

29:37.543 --> 29:39.076
And about the children,

29:39.078 --> 29:40.544
I'd like to ask you
one more time

29:40.546 --> 29:42.579
If teddy can split his time
between us.

29:42.581 --> 29:44.281
